{
  "stem": "4670.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was slowly at first, and then it became a very rapid kind of movement.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And what happened then was that my dad had to look for something else.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he decided to open a leather goods store, because that's something they'd had when they first came to Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was experienced.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In 1933, a boycott was presented to all of Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And in Frankfurt, of course, the boycott had to-- had to be done, too.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I don't think I'll ever forget that day because it was in April of 1933, when I was there, when the boycott was going on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I had left school and I was in the back room and doing homework, and my sister, my oldest sister, Renata, she was a sales girl.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And my sister Margot was in the back, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She was doing her homework, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "My dad was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I don't think there was anyone else.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Except, you know, at that time, we still had the [NON-ENGLISH], that means the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In other words, the police were still there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They had already had the SA Stormtrooper and the SS ones.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They were just beginning to exist.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But the police still was protecting the people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The police had known my dad for many years and he knew us well.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But the-- since it was-- you know, the boycott was in existence, the SR had to stand in front of the stores.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And, of course, it was well-publicized.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And they had signs up, you know, that people shouldn't buy there because it was a Jewish store.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And if there wasn't a sign up, well, then someone had to station themselves in front of the store.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
